  "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "To simplify block snapshots creation process please allow to sync blocks without executing them.\r\n1. In the past Erigon was able to do so: It did run `STOP_BEFORE_STAGE=Execution`\r\n2. In the past Erigon was able to sync blocks in 1-st sync cycle, now in 1-st cycle it executing blocks from snapshots, in 2-nd downloading and executing blocks in 1-transaction (and loosing all downloaded blocks if restart)\r\n3. erigon also has ` --force.partial.commit` flag, see https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/pull/8299",
